==English==
===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|xh|ísíXhosa|(ísí)Xhosa|t=Xhosa language}} and {{m|xh|úḿXhosa|(úḿ)Xhosa|t=Xhosa person}}, where the sequence ''xh'' denotes a click ({{IPAchar|/ˈǁʰoːsa/}}): {{audio-pron|xh|Xhosa.ogg|nocat=1}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|en|/ˈkoʊ.sə/}},<ref name="OADL">[http://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/xhosa Oxford Advanced learner's Dictionary]</ref><ref name="MacM">{{R:Macmillan}}</ref><ref name="Dictcom">{{R:Dictionary.com}}</ref> {{IPAchar|/ˈkɔ.sə/}}<ref name="MacM"/><ref name="Dictcom"/>
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/ˈkəʊ.sə/}},<ref name="MacM"/> {{IPAchar|/ˈkɔː.sə/|lang=en}}<ref name="OADL"/><ref name="MacM"/>
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|~|s|Xhosa}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} Any member of a [[Bantu]] [[people]] from [[South Africa]], most of whom live in the [[Eastern Cape]].
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[language]] of these people, a [[Bantu]] language related to [[Zulu]].
